main event: A report was made regarding an unidentified flying object sighted in Columbia, Kentucky on October 3, 1968.
interesting points: The reported object was approximately 600 feet in diameter and very brilliant., The observation was communicated via a call received by Mr. Stanley, the property owner., The Air Force deemed the information insufficient for a scientific investigation., The report was documented by Sgt. Doughty., The case was associated with Project Blue Book, which aimed to investigate UFO sightings from 1952 to 1969.
witness description: Mr. Stanley, the property owner who reported the observation
